 Dutywa - Dutywa police have appealed to the public to assist them with information that will help them trace a missing teenage girl. "It is alleged that 17-year-old Othemba Madaka was last seen on the 06 October 2019 at about 15h00 at Ngwenyama Locality, Nyhwarha Village, Dutywa," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "Anyone, who can assist Dutywa Police is kindly requested to contact 047 489 1333." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 